### CityVoice – Reports & Categories API Tests
### Compatible with: IntelliJ HTTP Client (native), kulala.nvim (ignores > {% %} blocks)
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api
###
### ⚠ SETUP ORDER:
###   1. Run "0a. Admin Login"   → adminToken stored globally
###   2. Run "0b. Citizen Login" → citizenToken stored globally
###   3. Run tests in section order
###
### 📎 POST /reports (sections 2a–2e):
###   Binary file uploads require curl -F. Provided as runnable shell commands.
###   IntelliJ: run via Tools → HTTP Client → Run in terminal.
###   kulala: yank command, run in terminal with :!
###
### NOTE: Sections 2–4 require a verified citizen account.
###   Use auth.http §4 to register + verify first.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@adminEmail = admin@cityvoice.vn
@adminPassword = Admin@123
@citizenEmail = finnzxje@gmail.com
@citizenPassword = Test@12345


# ─── 0. TOKEN SETUP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 0a. Admin login (stores adminToken globally)
# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/staff/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("adminToken", response.body.data.accessToken);
  client.test("Login OK",       () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
  client.test("Has accessToken",() => client.assert(response.body.data.accessToken !== ""));
%}

###

### 0b. Citizen login (stores citizenToken globally)
### ⚠ Requires a verified citizen account — use auth.http §4 first
# @name citizenLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/citizen/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{citizenEmail}}",
  "password": "{{citizenPassword}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("citizenToken", response.body.data.accessToken);
  client.test("Login OK",       () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
  client.test("Has accessToken",() => client.assert(response.body.data.accessToken !== ""));
%}


# ─── 1. CATEGORIES ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1a. List active categories – expect 200, non-empty array
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

> {%
  client.test("Status 200",      () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
  client.test("Returns array",   () => client.assert(Array.isArray(response.body.data)));
  client.test("Has items",       () => client.assert(response.body.data.length > 0));
  client.test("Has id/name/slug",() => {
    const c = response.body.data[0];
    client.assert(c.id   !== undefined);
    client.assert(c.name !== undefined);
    client.assert(c.slug !== undefined);
  });
  client.global.set("categoryId", response.body.data[0].id);
%}

###

### 1b. No token → 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories

> {%
  client.test("Status 401", () => client.assert(response.status === 401));
%}


# ─── 2. SUBMIT REPORT ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Binary file uploads cannot be sent reliably via raw .http multipart bodies.
# Use the curl commands below — binary encoding is handled correctly by curl -F.
#
# Set CITIZEN_TOKEN / ADMIN_TOKEN in your shell first:
#   export CITIZEN_TOKEN=$(cat /tmp/citizen_token.txt)   # or paste directly
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 2a. CITIZEN – valid HCMC location → Expect: 201 Created
### ↓ Run this in your terminal (replace $CITIZEN_TOKEN):
# curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/reports \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer $CITIZEN_TOKEN" \
#   -F "title=Pothole on Nguyen Hue Boulevard" \
#   -F "description=Large pothole causing traffic disruption near Quan 1" \
#   -F "categoryId=1" \
#   -F "latitude=10.7769" \
#   -F "longitude=106.7009" \
#   -F "image=@./backend/http/test_image.jpg;type=image/jpeg" | python3 -m json.tool
# → Copy `id` from response into {{reportId}} below

###

### 2b. ADMIN submits report → Expect: 403 Forbidden
# curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/reports \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer $ADMIN_TOKEN" \
#   -F "title=Admin test" -F "categoryId=1" \
#   -F "latitude=10.7769" -F "longitude=106.7009" \
#   -F "image=@./backend/http/test_image.jpg;type=image/jpeg"

###

### 2c. CITIZEN – Hanoi coordinates (outside HCMC) → Expect: 400
# curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/reports \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer $CITIZEN_TOKEN" \
#   -F "title=Out of bounds" -F "categoryId=1" \
#   -F "latitude=21.0" -F "longitude=105.8" \
#   -F "image=@./backend/http/test_image.jpg;type=image/jpeg" | python3 -m json.tool

###

### 2d. Missing required fields → Expect: 400 with `errors` object
# curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/reports \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer $CITIZEN_TOKEN" \
#   -F "latitude=10.7769" | python3 -m json.tool

###

### 2e. Invalid categoryId=99999 → Expect: 400
# curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/reports \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer $CITIZEN_TOKEN" \
#   -F "title=Bad Category" -F "categoryId=99999" \
#   -F "latitude=10.7769" -F "longitude=106.7009" \
#   -F "image=@./backend/http/test_image.jpg;type=image/jpeg" | python3 -m json.tool


# ─── 3. LIST OWN REPORTS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3a. CITIZEN lists their reports – expect 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/my
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}

> {%
  client.test("Status 200",    () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
  client.test("Returns array", () => client.assert(Array.isArray(response.body.data)));
%}

###

### 3b. ADMIN – citizen-only → expect 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/my
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

> {%
  client.test("Status 403", () => client.assert(response.status === 403));
%}

###

### 3c. No token → 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/my

> {%
  client.test("Status 401", () => client.assert(response.status === 401));
%}


# ─── 4. GET REPORT BY ID ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠ Run curl 2a first and paste the returned UUID into {{reportId}} below
@reportId = d5ef065a-e18b-43f2-b23d-4190589bea6f

### 4a. Owning CITIZEN fetches report – expect 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/{{reportId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}

> {%
  client.test("Status 200",           () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
  client.test("ID matches",           () => client.assert(response.body.data.id === client.global.get("reportId")));
  client.test("Status newly_received",() => client.assert(response.body.data.currentStatus === "newly_received"));
  client.test("Has imageUrl",         () => client.assert(!!response.body.data.incidentImageUrl));
%}

###

### 4b. ADMIN fetches any report – expect 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/{{reportId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

> {%
  client.test("Status 200", () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
%}

###

### 4c. Non-existent UUID – expect 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}

> {%
  client.test("Status 404", () => client.assert(response.status === 404));
%}

###

### 4d. No token – expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/{{reportId}}

> {%
  client.test("Status 401", () => client.assert(response.status === 401));
%}
